   288тЖТ/// The `Error` type, a wrapper around a dynamic error type.
   289тЖТ///
   290тЖТ/// `Error` works a lot like `Box<dyn std::error::Error>`, but with these
   291тЖТ/// differences:
   292тЖТ///
   293тЖТ/// - `Error` requires that the error is `Send`, `Sync`, and `'static`.
   294тЖТ/// - `Error` guarantees that a backtrace is available, even if the underlying
   295тЖТ///   error type does not provide one.
   296тЖТ/// - `Error` is represented as a narrow pointer &mdash; exactly one word in
   297тЖТ///   size instead of two.
   298тЖТ///
   299тЖТ/// <br>
   300тЖТ///
   301тЖТ/// # Display representations
   302тЖТ///
      тЖТтАж
